<div class="c230_49">
<div id="v230.49.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H4210 s">, A Psalm</span><span class="H1121 s"> for the sons</span><span class="H7141 s"> of Korah</span><span class="H8085 s">. Hear</span><span class="H5971 s"> this, all <i>ye</i> people</span><span class="H238 s">; give ear</span><span class="H3427 s">, all <i>ye</i> inhabitants</span><span class="H2465 s"> of the world</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (for: or, of)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.2"><span class="H1121 s">Both low</span><span class="H120 s"> †</span><span class="H1121 s"> and high</span><span class="H376 s"> †</span><span class="H6223 s">, rich</span><span class="H34 s"> and poor</span><span class="H3162 s">, together</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.49.3"><span class="H6310 s">My mouth</span><span class="H1696 s"> shall speak</span><span class="H2454 s"> of wisdom</span><span class="H1900 s">; and the meditation</span><span class="H3820 s"> of my heart</span><span class="H8394 s"> <i>shall be</i> of understanding</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.49.4"><span class="H5186 s">I will incline</span><span class="H241 s"> mine ear</span><span class="H4912 s"> to a parable</span><span class="H6605 s">: I will open</span><span class="H2420 s"> my dark saying</span><span class="H3658 s"> upon the harp</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.49.5"><span class="H3372 s">Wherefore should I fear</span><span class="H3117 s"> in the days</span><span class="H7451 s"> of evil</span><span class="H5771 s">, <i>when</i> the iniquity</span><span class="H6120 s"> of my heels</span><span class="H5437 s"> shall compass</span> me about?</div>
<div id="v230.49.6"><span class="H982 s">They that trust</span><span class="H2428 s"> in their wealth</span><span class="H1984 s">, and boast</span><span class="H7230 s"> themselves in the multitude</span><span class="H6239 s"> of their riches</span>;</div>
<div id="v230.49.7"><span class="H376 s">None <i>of them</i> can</span><span class="H6299 s"> by any means</span><span class="H6299 s"> redeem</span><span class="H251 s"> his brother</span><span class="H5414 s">, nor give</span><span class="H430 s"> to God</span><span class="H3724 s"> a ransom</span> for him:</div>
<div id="v230.49.8"><span class="H6306 s">(For the redemption</span><span class="H5315 s"> of their soul</span><span class="H3365 s"> <i>is</i> precious</span><span class="H2308 s">, and it ceaseth</span><span class="H5769 s"> for ever</span>:)</div>
<div id="v230.49.9"><span class="H2421 s">That he should still live</span><span class="H5331 s"> for ever</span><span class="H7200 s">, <i>and</i> not see</span><span class="H7845 s"> corruption</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.49.10"><span class="H7200 s">For he seeth</span><span class="H2450 s"> <i>that</i> wise men</span><span class="H4191 s"> die</span><span class="H3162 s">, likewise</span><span class="H3684 s"> the fool</span><span class="H1198 s"> and the brutish person</span><span class="H6 s"> perish</span><span class="H5800 s">, and leave</span><span class="H2428 s"> their wealth</span><span class="H312 s"> to others</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.49.11"><span class="H7130 s">Their inward</span><span class="H1004 s"> thought <i>is, that</i> their houses</span><span class="H5769 s"> <i>shall continue</i> for ever</span><span class="H4908 s">, <i>and</i> their dwelling</span><span class="H1755 s"> places to all</span><span class="H1755 s"> generations</span><span class="H7121 s">; they call</span><span class="H127 s"> <i>their</i> lands</span><span class="H8034 s"> after their own names</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (all…: Heb. generation and generation)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.12"><span class="H120 s">Nevertheless man</span><span class="H3366 s"> <i>being</i> in honour</span><span class="H3885 s"> abideth</span><span class="H4911 s"> not: he is like</span><span class="H929 s"> the beasts</span><span class="H1820 s"> <i>that</i> perish</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.49.13"><span class="H1870 s">This their way</span><span class="H3689 s"> <i>is</i> their folly</span><span class="H310 s">: yet their posterity</span><span class="H7521 s"> approve</span><span class="H6310 s"> their sayings</span><span class="H5542 s">. Selah</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (approve…: Heb. delight in their mouth)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.14"><span class="H6629 s">Like sheep</span><span class="H8371 s"> they are laid</span><span class="H7585 s"> in the grave</span><span class="H4194 s">; death</span><span class="H7462 s"> shall feed</span><span class="H3477 s"> on them; and the upright</span><span class="H7287 s"> shall have dominion</span><span class="H1242 s"> over them in the morning</span><span class="H6697 s">; and their beauty</span><span class="H6736 s"> †</span><span class="H1086 s"> shall consume</span><span class="H7585 s"> in the grave</span><span class="H2073 s"> from their dwelling</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (beauty: or, strength) (in the grave from…: or, the grave being an habitation to every one of them)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.15"><span class="H430 s">But God</span><span class="H6299 s"> will redeem</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H3027 s"> from the power</span><span class="H7585 s"> of the grave</span><span class="H3947 s">: for he shall receive</span><span class="H5542 s"> me. Selah</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (power: Heb. hand) (the grave: or, hell)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.16"><span class="H3372 s">Be not thou afraid</span><span class="H376 s"> when one</span><span class="H6238 s"> is made rich</span><span class="H3519 s">, when the glory</span><span class="H1004 s"> of his house</span><span class="H7235 s"> is increased</span>;</div>
<div id="v230.49.17"><span class="H4194 s">For when he dieth</span><span class="H3947 s"> he shall carry nothing away</span><span class="H3519 s">: his glory</span><span class="H3381 s"> shall not descend</span><span class="H310 s"> after</span> him.</div>
<div id="v230.49.18"><span class="H2416 s">Though while he lived</span><span class="H1288 s"> he blessed</span><span class="H5315 s"> his soul</span><span class="H3034 s">: and <i>men</i> will praise</span><span class="H3190 s"> thee, when thou doest well</span> to thyself. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (while…: Heb. in his life)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.19"><span class="H935 s">He shall go</span><span class="H1755 s"> to the generation</span><span class="H1 s"> of his fathers</span><span class="H3808 s">; they shall never</span><span class="H5331 s"> †</span><span class="H7200 s"> see</span><span class="H216 s"> light</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (He…: Heb. The soul shall)</span></div>
<div id="v230.49.20"><span class="H120 s">Man</span><span class="H3366 s"> <i>that is</i> in honour</span><span class="H995 s">, and understandeth</span><span class="H4911 s"> not, is like</span><span class="H929 s"> the beasts</span><span class="H1820 s"> <i>that</i> perish</span>.</div></div>
